Source: snooze
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Snooze maintainers <dev@snoozeweb.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13),
               golang-go (>= 1.25)
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Homepage: https://github.com/snoozeweb/snooze
Vcs-Browser: https://github.com/snoozeweb/snooze
Vcs-Git: https://github.com/snoozeweb/snooze.git
Rules-Requires-Root: no

Package: snooze-server
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, adduser
Description: Snooze alert routing server (Go rewrite)
 Snooze is an alert routing and aggregation platform. This package ships
 the main HTTP/API server daemon that owns the alert database, applies
 rules, and dispatches notifications.

Package: snooze
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Snooze command-line client
 Command-line client for interacting with a Snooze server (querying
 alerts, managing rules, acknowledging records, administrative tasks).

Package: snooze-syslog
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, snooze-server
Description: Snooze syslog ingestion daemon
 Listens for RFC 3164/5424 syslog messages over UDP/TCP and forwards
 parsed events into the Snooze server.

Package: snooze-snmptrap
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, snooze-server
Description: Snooze SNMP trap ingestion daemon
 Receives SNMPv1/v2c/v3 traps, resolves them against compiled MIBs and
 forwards the resulting events into the Snooze server.

Package: snooze-smtp
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, snooze-server
Description: Snooze SMTP ingestion daemon
 Accepts inbound mail and converts each message into a Snooze event.

Package: snooze-relp
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, snooze-server
Description: Snooze RELP ingestion daemon
 Receives reliable event-logging protocol (RELP) messages and forwards
 them into the Snooze server.

Package: snooze-googlechat
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, snooze-server
Description: Snooze Google Chat notification daemon
 Dispatches Snooze notifications to Google Chat spaces via incoming
 webhooks.

Package: snooze-mattermost
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, snooze-server
Description: Snooze Mattermost notification daemon
 Dispatches Snooze notifications to Mattermost channels via incoming
 webhooks.

Package: snooze-teams
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, snooze-server
Description: Snooze Microsoft Teams notification daemon
 Dispatches Snooze notifications to Microsoft Teams channels via
 workflow / incoming webhooks.

Package: snooze-pacemaker
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Snooze Pacemaker resource agent helper
 Helper binary used by Pacemaker resource agents to manage failover of
 Snooze daemons in clustered deployments.

Package: snooze-jira
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, snooze-server
Description: Snooze JIRA notification daemon
 Creates and updates JIRA Cloud tickets from Snooze alerts and (optionally)
 closes Snooze records when the corresponding JIRA ticket is resolved.
